\f1\fs32 The induced voltage is typically generated at a fixed frequency, such as 60 Hz in the United States.\
To generate three-phase power, the stator is fitted with three windings arranged symmetrically, 120 degrees apart from each other. As the rotor rotates, the rotating magnetic field induces voltages into each stator winding in turn, generating three sine waves of voltage, equally spaced, shown in <xref ref="three-phase"/>. \
